<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Sickles reports that the consul-general at Barcelona considers it
                            important to know immediately if the Department means by “Cubans and
                            Porto Ricans” resident inhabitants only, or if it means also persons
                            born in those islands, but resident since for some years in Spain.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>